06086nam a22008655i 9783110684384DE-B159720210526051534.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210526t20202020gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831106843847 a10.1515/97831106843842doi  a(DE-B1597)539592  a(OCoLC)1198929253  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aInternet AccessbAEU 7aLIT0120002bisacsh00aHandbook of Stemmatology :bHistory, Methodology, Digital Approaches /ced. by Philipp Roelli. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (VI, 688 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aDe Gruyter Reference00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- t1 Textual traditions -- t2 The genealogical method -- t3 Towards the construction of a stemma -- t4 The stemma -- t5 Computational methods and tools -- t6 Editions -- t7 Philological practices -- t8 Evolutionary models in other disciplines -- tTerminology in other languages -- tReferences -- tGeneral Index -- tIndex of Manuscripts -- tList of authors0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aStemmatology studies aspects of textual criticism that use genealogical methods to analyse a set of copies of a text whose autograph has been lost. This handbook is the first to cover the entire field, encompassing both theoretical and practical aspects of traditional as well as modern digital methods and their history. As an art (ars), stemmatology's main goal is editing and thus presenting to the reader a historical text in the most satisfactory way. As a more abstract discipline (scientia), it is interested in the general principles of how texts change in the process of being copied. Thirty eight experts from all of the fields involved have joined forces to write this handbook, whose eight chapters cover material aspects of text traditions, the genesis and methods of traditional "Lachmannian" textual criticism and the objections raised against it, as well as modern digital methods used in the field. The two concluding chapters take a closer look at how this approach towards texts and textual criticism has developed in some disciplines of textual scholarship and compare methods used in other fields that deal with "descent with modification". The handbook thus serves as an introduction to this interdisciplinary field.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCriticism, Textual. 0aTransmission of texts. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Reference.2bisacsh  aLachmann's method.  aTextual criticism.  adescent with modification.  astemmatology.1 aAndrews, Tara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuzzoni, Marina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConti, Aidan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGöransson, Elisabet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaugen, Odd Einar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoenen, Armin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacé, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoelli, Philipp, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZundert, Joris van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2020z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook